June 2026: version 0.5.0
        Breaking changes:
        * Fix bug in star(A): the input matrix was silently mutated
          (aliasing of A inside star). star() now operates on a copy and
          leaves its argument untouched. Code relying on the side effect
          (none expected) will see a behavioural change.
        * Fix bug in star(A): increased the number of squarings from
          O(log n) to ~2*log(n)+1 so that positive circuits are both
          detected and propagated. Previously, matrices with a positive
          cycle longer than ~log2(n) returned a finite result instead of
          a matrix saturated with +Inf.
        * Make star() generic in the float parameter T (Float32 / Float64).
          The internal "top" value no longer uses the hard-coded Float64
          mptop constant.
        Tests:
        * Add a non-regression test for the star() aliasing bug.
        * Add a non-regression test for the positive Hamiltonian cycle
          (sparse 5x5 with cycle weight 1) which must saturate to +Inf.
        * Fix several incorrect @test_broken cases in test_maxplus.jl
          (broken test ligne 877 was using mi0 in a max-plus matrix, and
          the spzeros tests were guarded by an outdated Julia 1.6 note).
        * Fix the min-plus border cases in test_minplus.jl: the previous
          expectations were not consistent with the (min,+) convention
          (mi0 = +Inf is absorbing for tensor product, mitop = -Inf is
          the top). All 16 broken cases for *, /, \ on mi0/mi1/mitop now
          pass with corrected expected values.
        * Add test/test_flowshop.jl: dedicated unit tests for the
          flowshop function using the workload from the
          TimedPetriNetEditor companion example "complex.flowshop"
          (8 machines × 6 pieces). Asserts the critical cycle (Howard
          eigenvalue) is 16.95 time units and that the closed-loop graph
          has a single strongly connected component.

April 2026: version 0.4.0
        * Julia 1.10 or later required
        * Removed dependencies PrettyTables and LaTeXStrings; add them to your project if needed
        * Update Tropical to be accepted by Graphs.jl
        * Epsilon is a TropicalZero singleton; review comparisons and ops with absorbing elements vs old epsilon = mp0
        * Reworked syslin, add flowshop, semi-Howard
        * fallbacks.jl simplified

April 2024: version 0.3.1
        * Update code because PrettyTables changed of API.

March 2023: version 0.3.0
        * It was a huge time to make a new version :)
        * Major API change and code refacto
        * Add (min,+) algebra
        * Translate tutorials

September 2019: version 0.2.0
        * French documentation
